So that the Law has nothing to say to the Christian should make sense
to anyone familiar with Romans 7:4, which reads, "So, my brothers and
sisters, you also died to the law through the body of Christ..."
Naturally, the law does not speak to the dead, among whom we number by
faith. Furthermore, how could that which is not of faith ("and the law
is not of faith," Galatians 3:12) have anything to add to us, to whom "whatsoever
is not of faith is sin" (Romans 14:23)?


